01:13:13,923 --> 01:13:15,822
Back up. Back up.

484
01:14:32,935 --> 01:14:34,245
Jean!

485
01:14:35,938 --> 01:14:37,018
Oh, God.

486
01:15:37,099 --> 01:15:39,029
Don't move.

487
01:15:55,985 --> 01:15:58,325
Don't you people ever die?

488
01:16:31,654 --> 01:16:35,694
Do you know what happens to a toad
when it's struck by lightning?

489
01:16:41,897 --> 01:16:44,857
The same thing
that happens to everything else.

490
01:16:59,849 --> 01:17:01,959
Logan, is that you?

491
01:17:13,662 --> 01:17:16,292
The other one ain't far away.

492
01:17:16,799 --> 01:17:20,609
- Come on. We have to regroup.
- [ know, but there's a problem.

493
01:17:24,406 --> 01:17:26,596
You're not part of the group.

494
01:17:48,898 --> 01:17:49,978
It's me.

495
01:17:50,299 --> 01:17:52,439
- Prove it.
- You're a dick.

496
01:17:54,003 --> 01:17:55,643
OK.

497
01:18:17,993 --> 01:18:20,713
- Everybody get out of here.
- What is it?

498
01:18:21,230 --> 01:18:23,009
I can't move.

499
01:18:44,186 --> 01:18:46,436
My brothers. Welcome.

500
01:18:47,957 --> 01:18:51,467
And you, just point those claws
of yours in a safer direction.

501
01:19:05,841 --> 01:19:07,771
You better close your eyes.

502
01:19:11,213 --> 01:19:12,822
Storm, fry 'em.

503
01:19:13,215 --> 01:19:19,665
A bolt of lightning into a huge copper
conductor. I thought you lived at a school.

504
01:19:25,794 --> 01:19:29,364
For those of you not familiar
with the historical significance...

505
01:19:34,436 --> 01:19:36,186
Mystique?

506
01:19:37,273 --> 01:19:40,613
- Mystique.
- I've seen Senator Kelly.

507
01:19:41,744 --> 01:19:46,603
So, the good senator survived his fall.
And the swim to shore.

508
01:19:47,449 --> 01:19:49,699
He's become even more powerful
than I imagined.

509
01:19:50,152 --> 01:19:52,462
- He's dead.
- It's true.

510
01:19:52,921 --> 01:19:56,521
I saw him die.
Like those people down there will die.

511
01:19:57,860 --> 01:20:00,349
Are you sure you saw what you saw?

512
01:20:00,863 --> 01:20:04,583
1 would also like to thank the
President of the United States of America

513
01:20:05,267 --> 01:20:10,277
for hosting this event under the lights
of the great city of New York.

514
01:20:18,347 --> 01:20:21,807
Why do none of you understand
what I'm trying to do?

515
01:20:22,451 --> 01:20:27,251
Those people down there control our fate
and the fate of every other mutant.

516
01:20:29,358 --> 01:20:31,258
Well,

517
01:20:31,727 --> 01:20:33,947
soon our fate will be theirs.

518
01:20:34,396 --> 01:20:37,266
Help! Please help me!

519
01:20:38,467 --> 01:20:43,267
You're so full of shit. If you're really
so righteous, it'd be you in that thing.

520
01:20:46,075 --> 01:20:49,205
Help! Somebody help me!

521
01:21:02,524 --> 01:21:04,274
Please!

522
01:21:06,128 --> 01:21:08,968
Somebody please help me!

523
01:21:13,836 --> 01:21:16,826
Somebody! Help me...

524
01:21:28,450 --> 01:21:30,500
Logan!

525
01:22:26,208 --> 01:22:29,138
- I'm sorry, my dear.
- Don't do this.

526
01:22:42,024 --> 01:22:43,774
This is mine.

527
01:23:46,989 --> 01:23:48,829
You owe me a scream.

528
01:23:52,694 --> 01:23:55,974
Hey, bub, I'm not finished with you yet.

529
01:24:00,135 --> 01:24:02,505
- Jean.
- Scott, when I tell you, open your eyes.

530
01:24:02,971 --> 01:24:03,821
- No.
- Trust me.

531
01:24:04,106 --> 01:24:06,326
You drop something?

532
01:24:10,579 --> 01:24:12,358
Now!

533
01:24:26,762 --> 01:24:28,602
- Thanks.
- Don't mention it.

534
01:24:29,565 --> 01:24:33,514
- Gotta get her outta there. Can you hit it?
- The rings are moving too fast.

535
01:24:34,202 --> 01:24:36,632
- Shoot it.
- I'll kill her! Storm, can you get me up?

536
01:24:37,139 --> 01:24:39,949
- l can't control it like that.
- Then let me go.

537
01:24:42,044 --> 01:24:46,494
If I don't make it,
at least you can still blast the damn thing.

538
01:24:47,983 --> 01:24:51,493
All right, do it.
Jean, use your power. Try to steady him.

539
01:24:53,622 --> 01:24:55,402
Hang on to something.

540
01:25:50,212 --> 01:25:52,492
Scott, wait!

541
01:26:22,210 --> 01:26:24,260
- Jean, I have to!
- Just wait!

542
01:26:26,448 --> 01:26:28,668
I have a shot.

543
01:26:29,117 --> 01:26:30,757
I'm taking it.

544
01:27:11,259 --> 01:27:13,369
Come on...

545
01:28:44,619 --> 01:28:47,339
This one's alive. Let's get him outta here.

546
01:29:13,682 --> 01:29:17,222
Welcome back. I knew you'd find your way.

547
01:29:17,853 --> 01:29:19,603
I had you to guide me.

548
01:29:23,024 --> 01:29:25,164
How did we do?

549
01:29:53,555 --> 01:29:55,395
That tickles.

550
01:29:55,824 --> 01:29:57,574
Hey.

551
01:30:00,896 --> 01:30:02,646
How are you feeling?

552
01:30:03,064 --> 01:30:04,844
Fantastic.

553
01:30:06,368 --> 01:30:08,588
That was a brave thing you did.

554
01:30:10,305 --> 01:30:12,585
- Did it work?
- Yeah.

555
01:30:13,074 --> 01:30:19,053
She's fine. She took on a few of your
more charming personality traits for a while.

556
01:30:20,849 --> 01:30:22,989
But we lived through it.

557
01:30:25,887 --> 01:30:28,166
I think she's a little taken with you.

558
01:30:28,657 --> 01:30:32,577
Well, you can tell her
my heart belongs to someone else.

559
01:30:37,933 --> 01:30:39,923
You know, you and I...

560
01:30:40,335 --> 01:30:42,085
How's the professor?

561
01:30:44,306 --> 01:30:46,236
He's good.

562
01:30:46,675 --> 01:30:48,425
Good.

563
01:30:53,381 --> 01:30:57,191
There's an abandoned military compound
at Alkali Lake in the Canadian Rockies

564
01:30:57,886 --> 01:31:01,456
close to where we found you.
There's not much left but...

565
01:31:02,123 --> 01:31:04,263
you might find some answers.

566
01:31:06,761 --> 01:31:10,241
- Thank you.
- Are you going to say goodbye to them?

567
01:31:13,335 --> 01:31:16,085
The Mutant Registration Act
Jost its main proponent

568
01:31:16,604 --> 01:31:19,034
with the reversal of Senator Robert Kelly

569
01:31:19,541 --> 01:31:23,411
who until now had provided the loudest
voice in the cry for mutant registration.

570
01:31:24,112 --> 01:31:29,272
1 was wrong in this particular issue and!
hope, in time, l may be forgiven. Thank you.

571
01:31:30,151 --> 01:31:32,811
The Mutant Registration Act
continues to draw support...

572
01:31:33,355 --> 01:31:35,105
Mystique.

573
01:31:36,458 --> 01:31:38,237
Son of a bitch.

574
01:31:40,595 --> 01:31:45,395
«from many parents' rights groups
who feel threatened by unidentified mutants.

575
01:31:46,201 --> 01:31:51,941
In a related story, the body of Senator Kelly's
aide, Henry Guyrich, was found today.

576
01:31:52,874 --> 01:31:57,624
Preliminary coroner's reports seem to
indicate that Guyrich was mauled by a bear.

577
01:32:04,953 --> 01:32:07,993
- You running again?
- Not really.

578
01:32:09,557 --> 01:32:12,397
I have some things to take care of up north.

579
01:32:18,199 --> 01:32:20,159
I kinda like it.

580
01:32:24,472 --> 01:32:26,612
I don't want you to go.

581
01:32:40,221 --> 01:32:42,361
I'll be back for this.

582
01:33:20,762 --> 01:33:22,812
Doesn't it ever wake you in the night,

583
01:33:23,264 --> 01:33:27,654
the feeling that some day they will pass
that foolish law, or one just like it,

584
01:33:28,436 --> 01:33:30,246
and come for you?

585
01:33:30,672 --> 01:33:33,132
And your children?

586
01:33:36,277 --> 01:33:39,237
It does indeed.

587
01:33:43,351 --> 01:33:45,931
What do you do when you wake up to that?

588
01:33:46,454 --> 01:33:52,464
I feel a swell of pity for the poor soul who
comes to that school looking for trouble.

589
01:34:01,936 --> 01:34:03,686
Why do you come here, Charles?

590
01:34:04,105 --> 01:34:07,174
Why do you ask questions
to which you already know the answers?

591
01:34:07,742 --> 01:34:11,522
Oh, yes. Your continuing search for hope.

592
01:34:22,724 --> 01:34:26,064
You know this plastic prison of theirs
won't hold me forever.

593
01:34:26,694 --> 01:34:31,474
The war is still coming, Charles,
and I intend to fight it.

594
01:34:32,300 --> 01:34:35,260
By any means necessary.

595
01:34:35,803 --> 01:34:38,413
And I will always be there.

596
01:34:39,908 --> 01:34:42,048
Old friend.

597
01:43:22,329 --> 01:43:24,108
Subtitles by Visiontext

598
01:44:12,480 --> 01:44:14,230
